name: Steam Age

quests.name: Creosote
quests.description: The Coke Ovens byproduct is Creosote, an Fluid. You will need it to produce Lubricant.

quests.name: Starry Skies
quests.description:
To get in this Dim, you have to collect Resources in the Aether. 
The Frame is made out of Zanite Blocks. You need a Crow's Eye to ignite the portal.

quests.name: Cutting Machine
quests.description:
The cutting machine allows you to craft several things. With this machine you should be now able to craft the Diamond Funnel. 
It requires Lubricant to run.

quests.name: Invar
quests.description: In the Mixer, you can craft Invar now. You will need it to proceed to the Diamond Funnel.

quests.name: Mixing
quests.description: Craft a Mixer. A Mixer is an awesome Item to mix all kind of Fluids together, aswell as Items!

quests.name: Getting the Drill
quests.description: You can use a Bronze or Copper Drill to use the Quarry. Check out the Recipes and usages in REI.

quests.name: The Aether
quests.description: Travel to the Aether by forming a Portal out of Aethere Portal Frame Blocks. Ignite it with a Diamond Grinding Head.

quests.name: Computer
quests.description:
If you have some basic programming skils, you can try to automate things with Computers and Turtles.
Turtles can move around and break blocks if a tool is equipped.

quests.name: Steam Quarry
quests.description: As the Name tells you, a Quarry is required to mine Items out of the Air. You need Steam to run it. In addition, place the Quarry and hover with a MI Wrench over it.

quests.name: Steel Power
quests.description: Go ahead and give your Bronze Machines an Steel Upgrade. The Speed is almost 3x faster then Bronze.

quests.name: Pack and Unpacking
quests.description:
Steel also provides you 2 new Machines. The Packer and Unpacker.
While the Unpacker is dividing Items, the Packer puts them back together.

quests.name: Tanks
quests.description: Steel Tanks are able to store any kind of fluid in large amounts.

quests.name: 5x5 to 9x9 Crafting
quests.description:
Start by crafting an 5x5 crafting table, the Greater Table, you will need it for the Crow's Eye.
Later you will need larger tables with a grid of 7x7 and 9x9.

quests.name: Steam Buckets
quests.description: At this point you have no other choice to produce Steam in a Furnace by smelting a Water Bucket.

quests.name: Bronze Pump
quests.description: Use the Water Pump to pump water in the Bronze Boiler which will explained in the next quest.

quests.name: Coke Oven
quests.description: Build the Coke Oven multiblock structure to get coke. Please check the Guide Book to see how you can handle input/output.

quests.name: Item Pipes
quests.description: Now you can craft Steel Gears. You will need these for the construction of Item Pipes. You can place multiple Pipe types in one block.

quests.name: Compressor
quests.description: With the Compressor you can press all kind of Items into plates.

quests.name: Wiremill
quests.description: Craft a Steam Wiremill. You will need it for a lot of Wires within the next Age!

quests.name: Steel
quests.description: Build a Blast Furnace to get Steel. Check out the Mod Book to know the Shape and all other Details.

quests.name: Lubricant
quests.description: Create Lubricant in the Mixer with Creosote and Redstone.

quests.name: Modern Industrialisation
quests.description: Start by crafting a Forge Hammer.

quests.name: Next Gen Tools + Armor
quests.description: No shame here, but Steel opens up new Tools and Protection again. You might try them out.

quests.name: Diamond Funnel
quests.description: Now you should be able to upgrade to an Diamond Funnel. It will provide you with Lead and Antimony Ores. These materials are required to craft Batteries.

quests.name: Steel me Up!
quests.description: With Steel avaible now, you are going to become a lot stronger! Well... Maybe. Time to get some.

quests.name: Raw Oil
quests.description: To keep on progressing, you require synthetic Oil. Go ahead and get ur Mixer ready.

quests.name: Macerator
quests.description: Use the Macerator to grind down some Ingots or Jewels into dust.

quests.name: Coke
quests.description: To get Coke, you will need to burn Coal in the Coke Oven. Coal Dust works aswell and is even better for a few other Items.

quests.name: Better In- and Outputs
quests.description: If the Bronze In- or Outputs are to slow for you, just Upgrade those.

quests.name: Bronze Machine Casing
quests.description: For every Bronze Machine, you will need an Bronze Machine Casing.

quests.name: Syntetic Oil
quests.description: Produce some Syntetic Oil to get Rubber Sheets.

quests.name: Refined Iron
quests.description: You can get Refined Iron by smelting Iron Ingots in the Blast Furnace. This item will be useful once you've finished this capcher.

quests.name: Steel Machines
quests.description: You will need an Steel Machine Casing if you plan to upgrade your machines.

quests.name: Autocrafting
quests.description: You can automate crafting tasks with the Automated Crafting Table. It requires an Redstone-Puls to work.

quests.name: Bronze Boiler
quests.description:
The Mod Modern Industrialization will now accompany you for a while. The first thing you need is a boiler to produce steam.
You will need water to produce Steam. So use a Bronze Water Pump or any other water source you like.

description: In this chapter you will be guided through the mod "Modern Industrialization". From the basics such as the production of steam to complex electricity-driven machines. It's going to be a long way.
